1
00:00:41,897 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:49,696 --> 00:00:53,533
Have you heard of the ill-omened star?

3
00:00:53,617 --> 00:00:55,786
I'm sure you all remember
the recent cosmic show

4
00:00:55,869 --> 00:00:58,622
where a total solar eclipse
and a comet appeared together.

5
00:00:58,705 --> 00:01:02,751
Well, that comet is
still in the sky today.

6
00:01:02,834 --> 00:01:04,961
That's really amazing.

7
00:01:05,045 --> 00:01:06,296
Three hundred years ago,

8
00:01:06,380 --> 00:01:09,132
when our ancestors noticed a comet
lingering for two months,

9
00:01:09,216 --> 00:01:12,260
they called it the ill-omened star.

10
00:01:12,969 --> 00:01:16,765
The herald of a villainess
who brings disaster.

11
00:01:16,848 --> 00:01:18,684
You pity me?

12
00:01:42,874 --> 00:01:45,210
I guess he just can't ignore that woman.

13
00:01:45,711 --> 00:01:47,003
THE WOMAN POSSESSED BY KIM DU-HAN

14
00:01:49,214 --> 00:01:50,215
Unit 203?

15
00:01:50,298 --> 00:01:51,299
What the…

16
00:01:53,427 --> 00:01:55,095
She's resorted to throwing punches now.

17
00:01:55,178 --> 00:01:58,557
So, take a good look around you.

18
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,808
You never know.

19
00:01:59,891 --> 00:02:03,103
You might discover there's
a wicked woman living right next door.

20
00:02:03,645 --> 00:02:05,647
I have to keep my distance from her.

21
00:02:05,731 --> 00:02:07,733
That woman just creeps me out.

22
00:02:07,816 --> 00:02:10,736
He’s going to get
seriously tangled up with her.

23
00:02:11,528 --> 00:02:13,488
Why do our paths keep crossing?

24
00:02:13,572 --> 00:02:15,240
I'm about to lose it.

25
00:02:16,783 --> 00:02:19,202
EPISODE 5
FORBIDDEN FRUIT

26
00:02:19,286 --> 00:02:20,412
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

27
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:27,377
She acts like she's so smart.

28
00:02:28,003 --> 00:02:30,422
Did she just get scammed
by her realtor or what?

29
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:34,593
There's not even an elevator here.

30
00:02:38,221 --> 00:02:40,140
And the lights don't even work.

31
00:03:11,421 --> 00:03:12,506
Are you crying?

32
00:03:20,222 --> 00:03:23,016
Are you really crying,
hunched over like that?

33
00:03:32,484 --> 00:03:33,652
What?

34
00:03:34,444 --> 00:03:36,112
Why are you back to pick another fight?

35
00:03:36,196 --> 00:03:38,865
That's more like the Shin Seo-ri I know.

36
00:03:41,535 --> 00:03:44,996
So she's just some random model,
nothing more?

37
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:45,956
Yes, sir.

38
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:48,625
He was initially opposed to it,

39
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:51,169
but Director Jang
strongly recommended her.

40
00:03:51,253 --> 00:03:52,128
Really?

41
00:03:54,297 --> 00:03:56,091
I should've known better.

42
00:03:56,174 --> 00:03:59,511
What was he thinking,
linking my Se-gye with that woman?

43
00:04:11,648 --> 00:04:14,109
Are you still checking if you're unfazed?

44
00:04:14,192 --> 00:04:16,194
I think this is more than enough.

45
00:04:18,321 --> 00:04:19,948
No, I finished a while ago,

46
00:04:20,031 --> 00:04:21,241
but you were staying so still.

47
00:04:21,324 --> 00:04:23,285
I just thought you were still checking.

48
00:04:24,786 --> 00:04:26,329
I finished a while ago too.

49
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,166
Yeah?

50
00:04:34,087 --> 00:04:35,338
So what's the conclusion?

51
00:04:36,131 --> 00:04:39,676
Must you press me like a debt collector?

52
00:04:40,802 --> 00:04:42,304
I already told you.

53
00:04:42,387 --> 00:04:45,515
I see in black or white.
You're either an ally or an enemy.

54
00:04:45,599 --> 00:04:47,559
I hate it when men and women

55
00:04:47,642 --> 00:04:50,020
end up in that "just friends" gray area.

56
00:04:50,103 --> 00:04:51,563
So give it to me straight.

57
00:04:52,397 --> 00:04:55,650
Why should I go first? You answer first.

58
00:04:55,734 --> 00:04:56,860
Well…

59
00:04:58,737 --> 00:04:59,821
All right.

60
00:05:01,907 --> 00:05:04,618
It’s cowardly for a man
to expect a woman to make the first move.

61
00:05:04,701 --> 00:05:06,661
I hate it when things get predictable.

62
00:05:11,207 --> 00:05:12,334
All right.

63
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:15,837
I decided it's a green light

64
00:05:15,921 --> 00:05:16,963
for me.

65
00:05:21,509 --> 00:05:22,594
You turned on a lantern?

66
00:05:22,677 --> 00:05:24,638
I've decided to pursue you.

67
00:05:26,222 --> 00:05:27,557
Jeez.

68
00:05:31,061 --> 00:05:32,103
How do you feel?

69
00:05:32,729 --> 00:05:33,688
Honored, right?

70
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:35,190
Heir to the Chail Group

71
00:05:35,273 --> 00:05:36,900
and the finest face
in the corporate world.

72
00:05:36,983 --> 00:05:39,402
I've had plenty of people declare
their love for me,

73
00:05:39,486 --> 00:05:41,821
but I've never gone
on the offensive like this.

74
00:05:45,575 --> 00:05:48,662
It seems you're so touched,
you can't even find the words.

75
00:05:49,245 --> 00:05:51,957
Well, I understand.
Your heart must've skipped a beat,

76
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,876
and your nerve endings
must be tingling like crazy, right?

77
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,961
Relish it.

78
00:05:56,044 --> 00:05:56,962
Because this is

79
00:05:57,045 --> 00:06:00,757
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity
for a woman like you.

80
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,470
I did not feel any tingling.

81
00:06:08,264 --> 00:06:11,768
It probably hasn't sunk in yet.
You're still reeling from the shock.

82
00:06:11,851 --> 00:06:13,228
Give it five minutes.

83
00:06:13,311 --> 00:06:14,729
Even your fingertips will tingle.

84
00:06:14,813 --> 00:06:16,898
Shin Seo-ri, you won't sleep tonight.

85
00:06:16,982 --> 00:06:18,775
I feel absolutely nothing.

86
00:06:19,401 --> 00:06:21,528
Even when we embraced, I felt nothing.

87
00:06:21,611 --> 00:06:23,863
That's impossible.

88
00:06:23,947 --> 00:06:27,367
You were just in the arms of a guy
like me, dripping with pheromones.

89
00:06:33,915 --> 00:06:35,583
Don't lie, Shin Seo-ri.

90
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:38,169
Don't put up a front now
and regret it later.

91
00:06:38,253 --> 00:06:40,296
This is no front.
I was just born strong-willed.

92
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:41,881
Also,

93
00:06:41,965 --> 00:06:44,426
I do not go around telling needless lies.

94
00:06:46,094 --> 00:06:48,054
Wait, are you serious?

95
00:06:51,349 --> 00:06:53,101
You really feel nothing?

96
00:06:53,184 --> 00:06:54,644
-Even after I hugged you?
-Nothing.

97
00:07:00,108 --> 00:07:01,818
That can't be right.

98
00:07:03,028 --> 00:07:06,072
You definitely should've felt what I felt.

99
00:07:14,497 --> 00:07:16,541
I wasn't going to ask you this,

100
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:19,586
but have you been perpetually single
your whole life?

101
00:07:21,171 --> 00:07:22,338
"Perpetually single"?

102
00:07:23,089 --> 00:07:24,799
Have you never dated a man before?

103
00:07:26,342 --> 00:07:27,218
As if.

104
00:07:27,302 --> 00:07:28,720
At this age? With this beauty?

105
00:07:28,803 --> 00:07:30,221
Like men would have left me alone.

106
00:07:30,305 --> 00:07:32,265
-Ridiculous.
-Right?

107
00:07:32,849 --> 00:07:33,850
Yeah.

108
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:37,020
Then why didn't you feel anything with me?

109
00:07:37,103 --> 00:07:38,813
Does asking repeatedly change anything?

110
00:07:38,897 --> 00:07:41,399
I do not see you as a man.

111
00:07:41,483 --> 00:07:42,817
That must be what it means.

112
00:07:50,241 --> 00:07:51,701
Wait, what?

113
00:07:51,785 --> 00:07:54,120
It is raining! Oh my.

114
00:08:18,228 --> 00:08:20,355
Keep a close eye on him.

115
00:08:20,438 --> 00:08:24,442
Mun-do wouldn't mention baseless rumors.

116
00:08:24,526 --> 00:08:27,112
That woman he saw at the TV station.

117
00:08:27,195 --> 00:08:29,405
Find out who she is.

118
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:34,744
At the station? Then it can only be her.

119
00:08:37,914 --> 00:08:39,332
True to your name, Degenerate.

120
00:08:39,415 --> 00:08:40,792
Even if it is raining,

121
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:43,545
you cannot just walk into the home
of a single woman who lives alone.

122
00:08:43,628 --> 00:08:45,672
-You really felt nothing?
-Are you still on that?

123
00:08:45,755 --> 00:08:47,882
That is right. I felt nothing.

124
00:08:47,966 --> 00:08:50,009
It was less thrilling
than hugging a stray mutt.

125
00:08:50,093 --> 00:08:51,344
"A mutt"?

126
00:08:51,427 --> 00:08:52,846
So stop moping around

127
00:08:52,929 --> 00:08:54,639
and go home!

128
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:59,811
Maybe you felt nothing
because it was too quick.

129
00:09:00,812 --> 00:09:02,605
You've been single for too long.

130
00:09:02,689 --> 00:09:05,900
Your romantic instincts are dead.
It sounds like you need a warm-up.

131
00:09:05,984 --> 00:09:07,610
Let's try again. Then I'm sure you'll--

132
00:09:07,694 --> 00:09:10,113
This is getting pitiful.
Just stop, Cha Se-gye.

133
00:09:10,864 --> 00:09:11,823
"Pitiful"?

134
00:09:13,032 --> 00:09:14,075
Me?

135
00:09:15,243 --> 00:09:17,912
They say never chase a maiden
who has walked away.

136
00:09:17,996 --> 00:09:19,164
This is my home,

137
00:09:19,247 --> 00:09:21,374
so just let it go gracefully.

138
00:09:23,042 --> 00:09:24,836
After not dating for so long,
you must've become

139
00:09:24,919 --> 00:09:26,254
romantically impotent.

140
00:09:26,337 --> 00:09:29,382
You must know an opportunity like this
is rarer than winning the lottery.

141
00:09:29,465 --> 00:09:31,593
Even with three generations of good karma,

142
00:09:32,385 --> 00:09:33,887
the chances of such a jackpot are slim.

143
00:09:33,970 --> 00:09:35,597
For one, I am not impotent.

144
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,765
And affection, love,
and marriage in this lifetime?

145
00:09:37,849 --> 00:09:39,392
I want no part of any of that.

146
00:09:39,475 --> 00:09:42,228
I never want to get involved
with a man again.

147
00:09:42,312 --> 00:09:45,273
So stop being so pathetically clingy.

148
00:09:45,356 --> 00:09:46,482
Jeez.

149
00:09:47,859 --> 00:09:49,277
"Pathetically"?

150
00:09:50,069 --> 00:09:51,613
Damn,

151
00:09:51,696 --> 00:09:53,948
you must think you have
the upper hand now or something.

152
00:09:54,032 --> 00:09:57,368
Shin Seo-ri, that's one hell
of a shift in attitude.

153
00:09:57,452 --> 00:09:59,037
What you just said.

154
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:02,207
I've permanently etched it
into my frontal lobe.

155
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:04,792
You can't ever take it back.

156
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:06,836
Do not worry about that.

157
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:09,005
Even in a game of janggi,

158
00:10:09,088 --> 00:10:12,008
I have never once asked
to take back a move.

159
00:10:16,095 --> 00:10:18,806
You're so damn immersed
in this Joseon woman roleplay

160
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:20,642
that you must've lost touch with reality.

161
00:10:20,725 --> 00:10:23,019
I will make sure…

162
00:10:25,188 --> 00:10:27,607
you regret this moment
for the rest of your life.

163
00:10:28,107 --> 00:10:29,192
I will.

164
00:10:34,239 --> 00:10:35,240
Damn it.

165
00:10:52,382 --> 00:10:54,926
My heart was about
to jump out of my chest.

166
00:10:55,009 --> 00:10:57,428
Why the hell
would he just embrace me like that?

167
00:10:59,597 --> 00:11:00,848
Don't you have an umbrella?

168
00:11:00,932 --> 00:11:01,891
No, I do not!

169
00:11:01,975 --> 00:11:04,102
What does this dump even have?

170
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:08,731
What is wrong with my home?

171
00:11:08,815 --> 00:11:10,984
It even has a clear view of Namsan Tower!

172
00:11:27,417 --> 00:11:29,002
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

173
00:11:35,174 --> 00:11:37,302
Who the hell did this?!

174
00:11:48,771 --> 00:11:50,773
That's a nasty scratch.

175
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:53,776
The repair cost will be insane.
You checked the dashcam, right?

176
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:55,236
Just take it in for repairs later.

177
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,572
Even a chaebol shouldn't let
something like this slide.

178
00:11:57,655 --> 00:11:59,866
Just forget it.
That dashcam might as well be a tin can.

179
00:11:59,949 --> 00:12:01,242
You didn't turn it on?

180
00:12:01,326 --> 00:12:04,370
How does someone as thorough
as you forget something like this?

181
00:12:04,454 --> 00:12:06,497
Do you really think I just forgot?

182
00:12:06,581 --> 00:12:09,375
I turned it off on purpose.
I mean, why would I leave evidence

183
00:12:09,459 --> 00:12:10,793
they could use against me?

184
00:12:16,632 --> 00:12:19,427
It's the dashcam footage nailing people
in these power-trip scandals.

185
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:22,096
Straight to the prosecutors
with nowhere to run.

186
00:12:22,722 --> 00:12:25,850
You should never leave a trail
to begin with.

187
00:12:28,061 --> 00:12:29,687
You're way too paranoid.

188
00:12:32,231 --> 00:12:33,107
BUILT-IN CAM

189
00:12:33,816 --> 00:12:34,692
NO MEMORY CARD

190
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:38,071
Sir, don't tell me
you don't trust me either.

191
00:12:38,154 --> 00:12:40,782
In today's world, isn't this level
of distrust the default?

192
00:12:40,865 --> 00:12:43,076
I don't trust anyone in this world.
You are not exempt.

193
00:12:43,159 --> 00:12:45,036
I only trust myself, no one else.

194
00:12:45,119 --> 00:12:48,247
You'll have a lonely life
if you keep living that way.

195
00:12:48,331 --> 00:12:52,210
I've had everything I could ever want.
What do I have to be lonely about?

196
00:12:52,293 --> 00:12:53,920
You don't have a woman.

197
00:12:54,504 --> 00:12:56,130
Destined to die alone.

198
00:13:00,468 --> 00:13:01,844
-Mr. Son.
-Yes, sir.

199
00:13:01,928 --> 00:13:04,138
It seems like I've let you
get too comfortable lately.

200
00:13:05,181 --> 00:13:08,643
We seem to have lost
all sense of hierarchy.

201
00:13:10,186 --> 00:13:11,687
-Watch yourself.
-I will watch myself.

202
00:13:11,771 --> 00:13:14,565
-Keep your eyes on the road.
-Keeping my eyes on the road.

203
00:13:15,358 --> 00:13:16,859
-Seer.
-Yes?

204
00:13:16,943 --> 00:13:19,362
I assume you prepared what I asked for?

205
00:13:20,863 --> 00:13:22,198
Of course.

206
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,210
There we go.

207
00:13:39,966 --> 00:13:41,968
Hold the elevator.

208
00:13:42,051 --> 00:13:45,096
Oh my. Good morning, Mr. Cha.

209
00:13:47,432 --> 00:13:50,059
Ms. Kim, you seem
awfully happy with life these days.

210
00:13:51,144 --> 00:13:53,396
"I don't smile because I'm happy.
I smile to be happy."

211
00:13:53,479 --> 00:13:54,689
That is my motto.

212
00:13:55,898 --> 00:13:59,360
You have time to gleefully find happiness
and energy to spare, I see.

213
00:14:00,361 --> 00:14:02,738
Then we can just cancel
your PTO this month, right?

214
00:14:02,822 --> 00:14:04,240
My PTO…

215
00:14:06,909 --> 00:14:11,080
I already booked a trip to Saipan
for my father-in-law's 70th.

216
00:14:11,164 --> 00:14:13,875
You have to go to that.
Pass him my congratulations.

217
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:18,087
They will appreciate a cozy getaway
without their daughter-in-law.

218
00:14:18,796 --> 00:14:22,300
Graciously sending them off on their own.
Isn't that true filial piety?

219
00:14:36,647 --> 00:14:38,941
Mr. Son, there's something
I don't understand.

220
00:14:39,025 --> 00:14:42,153
Why do we need snacks
and coffee in the break room?

221
00:14:42,236 --> 00:14:45,281
It's for staff welfare purposes.

222
00:14:45,364 --> 00:14:48,034
That's what salaries are for, isn't it?

223
00:14:48,117 --> 00:14:49,911
Should we be dedicating
such prime real estate

224
00:14:49,994 --> 00:14:53,206
to a snack corner just so employees
can munch away on company time?

225
00:14:53,289 --> 00:14:54,957
Close the break room immediately.

226
00:15:05,009 --> 00:15:07,261
Why is he in rabid dog mode again?

227
00:15:07,345 --> 00:15:09,347
Just when things were looking up.

228
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:11,140
Be careful at times like this.

229
00:15:11,224 --> 00:15:14,060
He's the type to let things build up
and explode all at once.

230
00:15:15,144 --> 00:15:17,438
-Mr. Son.
-Sir.

231
00:15:17,522 --> 00:15:19,732
I like those quick reflexes, Mr. Son.

232
00:15:19,815 --> 00:15:21,150
Stay on full standby.

233
00:15:25,196 --> 00:15:26,656
He's sick in the head.

234
00:15:32,537 --> 00:15:33,996
Is your cheek okay?

235
00:15:34,872 --> 00:15:37,124
I gave that punk Se-gye a real scolding.

236
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:39,001
Swinging at people like some common thug…

237
00:15:39,085 --> 00:15:40,336
I'm fine, Uncle.

238
00:15:41,546 --> 00:15:43,965
Mun-do, I must ask you to be
the bigger person.

239
00:15:44,549 --> 00:15:46,759
Don't worry. I understand.

240
00:15:48,219 --> 00:15:51,722
More importantly, the press release
for the Songjin Resort groundbreaking

241
00:15:51,806 --> 00:15:52,974
was received well.

242
00:15:53,057 --> 00:15:55,810
It's all thanks to your foresight.

243
00:15:55,893 --> 00:15:59,063
How many struggling subsidiaries
have you resurrected already?

244
00:16:00,898 --> 00:16:03,150
With you providing such solid support,

245
00:16:03,234 --> 00:16:04,902
I think it's about time

246
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:07,405
we start looking

247
00:16:07,488 --> 00:16:09,740
into the group succession issue.

248
00:16:09,824 --> 00:16:13,119
Just wrap up the resort deal well.

249
00:16:13,869 --> 00:16:15,037
Yes, sir.

250
00:16:15,705 --> 00:16:18,082
Chairman, Attorney Choi is here.

251
00:16:18,165 --> 00:16:19,125
Okay.

252
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:21,502
-You can go now.
-Yes, Uncle.

253
00:17:01,959 --> 00:17:03,294
They're notarized documents.

254
00:17:03,377 --> 00:17:05,713
They outline the full transfer
of Chairman Cha's shareholding

255
00:17:05,796 --> 00:17:07,006
across all subsidiaries,

256
00:17:07,089 --> 00:17:09,759
holding company included,
to Mr. Cha Se-gye.

257
00:17:09,842 --> 00:17:10,718
Does Se-gye know?

258
00:17:10,801 --> 00:17:12,553
Inheritance notarization can be processed

259
00:17:12,637 --> 00:17:14,972
with just a resident ID number.
No consent required.

260
00:17:15,056 --> 00:17:17,224
Chairman Cha didn't want
Mr. Cha to know about it.

261
00:17:21,979 --> 00:17:23,356
Our Chairman…

262
00:17:24,899 --> 00:17:26,984
sure loves his grandson fiercely.

263
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:37,745
Will using coagulated ox blood like this
really ward off bad luck?

264
00:17:37,828 --> 00:17:39,413
We must work with what we have got.

265
00:17:39,497 --> 00:17:42,583
You know, after 20 years as a seer,

266
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:44,377
there's one thing I've learned.

267
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:47,129
The cumulative law of suffering
does indeed exist.

268
00:17:47,213 --> 00:17:49,006
You found a job

269
00:17:49,090 --> 00:17:50,466
and even found yourself a home.

270
00:17:50,549 --> 00:17:52,259
I mean, just look at you.

271
00:17:52,343 --> 00:17:54,512
Seems like your days of hardship
are nearly done.

272
00:17:54,595 --> 00:17:56,597
Good luck invites bad. Such is life.

273
00:17:56,681 --> 00:17:58,057
Yes, of course.

274
00:17:58,140 --> 00:18:01,727
People will always find a way to stab you
in the back when you let your guard down.

275
00:18:01,811 --> 00:18:05,356
I am doing this warding ritual
so I can at least have some peace of mind.

276
00:18:07,566 --> 00:18:09,068
What warding ritual?

277
00:18:12,905 --> 00:18:16,283
At age 12, the day I was sold off
for my father's gambling debt,

278
00:18:16,826 --> 00:18:18,828
I learned my first life lesson.

279
00:18:19,787 --> 00:18:22,998
What a gloomy face on this girl.
Bad luck written all over it.

280
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,334
Keep acting this way,

281
00:18:25,418 --> 00:18:28,129
and there will be
nothing left of you to find.

282
00:18:28,212 --> 00:18:29,422
Jeez.

283
00:18:31,507 --> 00:18:32,925
Do not worry.

284
00:18:33,008 --> 00:18:36,220
Being a slave to a noble family
that keeps you fed

285
00:18:36,303 --> 00:18:38,472
beats starving at home
a hundred times over.

286
00:18:39,932 --> 00:18:41,183
Here.

287
00:18:41,726 --> 00:18:43,352
Go on. Have some.

288
00:18:44,061 --> 00:18:45,229
Just try it.

289
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:50,109
Crying on an empty stomach
will only exhaust you.

290
00:18:51,485 --> 00:18:53,237
My goodness.

291
00:18:54,905 --> 00:18:58,993
Free kindness always comes with a price.

292
00:18:59,076 --> 00:19:00,870
Here. That is plenty.

293
00:19:00,953 --> 00:19:04,123
Come on, I deserve
five more nyang for her.

294
00:19:04,206 --> 00:19:06,083
Look at that pretty face.

295
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:08,586
She will seduce plenty of men
when she grows up.

296
00:19:08,669 --> 00:19:10,546
If you sell her
to a courtesan house later,

297
00:19:10,629 --> 00:19:12,673
she will fetch you enough
to buy a house in Bukchon.

298
00:19:12,757 --> 00:19:14,508
-Trust me on this.
-Really? A house?

299
00:19:14,592 --> 00:19:18,304
Never trust a hand
reached out with a smile.

300
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,639
-What?
-Hey!

301
00:19:20,723 --> 00:19:22,683
-Hey!
-Where are you going?

302
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:23,809
You brat!

303
00:19:25,519 --> 00:19:26,812
Damn it.

304
00:19:26,896 --> 00:19:27,813
Unbelievable.

305
00:19:29,857 --> 00:19:30,733
Goodness.

306
00:19:30,816 --> 00:19:33,944
Lock her in the shed.
Do not give her a drop of water.

307
00:19:43,412 --> 00:19:45,164
I swore to myself back then

308
00:19:46,081 --> 00:19:49,877
that I would never trust
anyone but myself.

309
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:53,047
That I would never be sold off
like livestock again.

310
00:20:01,764 --> 00:20:04,433
I'm rooting for you two.

311
00:20:04,517 --> 00:20:06,185
I can promise you a real future.

312
00:20:06,936 --> 00:20:08,562
A life of comfort.

313
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:17,112
Wait, is someone trying
to sell you off here too?

314
00:20:17,196 --> 00:20:20,282
He promised a hefty reward
if I agreed to be sold.

315
00:20:21,784 --> 00:20:24,829
I will not make the mistake of falling

316
00:20:25,704 --> 00:20:27,289
for such sweet talk ever again.

317
00:20:30,751 --> 00:20:32,878
But don't you think
you'll get a little lonely

318
00:20:32,962 --> 00:20:34,505
if you live your life like that?

319
00:20:34,588 --> 00:20:36,924
Not all of them will turn out

320
00:20:37,007 --> 00:20:38,717
to be scammers.

321
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:41,470
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

322
00:20:44,557 --> 00:20:46,892
The world may be a harsh place,

323
00:20:46,976 --> 00:20:50,312
but not everyone in it means you harm.

324
00:20:53,691 --> 00:20:55,734
That is why I must steel my resolve.

325
00:20:56,652 --> 00:20:58,112
Scammer or not,

326
00:20:58,195 --> 00:21:00,281
once your heart wavers, you become weak.

327
00:21:00,364 --> 00:21:02,950
In my current situation,
weakness means the end.

328
00:21:03,659 --> 00:21:05,703
Thus, I have decided.

329
00:21:05,786 --> 00:21:07,955
In this life, I will not trust anyone.

330
00:21:08,038 --> 00:21:09,123
Instead, I shall become

331
00:21:09,206 --> 00:21:11,709
a wealthy Buddhist nun
on a path to enlightenment.

332
00:21:12,501 --> 00:21:15,921
A wealthy… Buddhist nun, you say?

333
00:21:17,131 --> 00:21:19,341
The only constant in this world is money.

334
00:21:19,425 --> 00:21:20,968
Ought we not serve it?

335
00:21:21,802 --> 00:21:25,055
When I open my window,
I can already see Namsan Tower.

336
00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:28,058
I escaped that dump
in the blink of an eye,

337
00:21:28,142 --> 00:21:31,270
so I shall use this momentum to soar high.

338
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:42,323
Sounds good!

339
00:21:49,204 --> 00:21:50,831
She feels nothing for me?

340
00:21:50,915 --> 00:21:53,250
Acting tough is only cute up to a point.

341
00:21:55,502 --> 00:21:58,964
She's the one who messed with my head
with that letter and everything.

342
00:22:00,341 --> 00:22:02,676
I've never been so humiliated in my life.

343
00:22:04,094 --> 00:22:05,971
Known as the heir to one of the top 30…

344
00:22:06,055 --> 00:22:07,139
What now?

345
00:22:07,222 --> 00:22:08,641
Controversy is brewing

346
00:22:08,724 --> 00:22:11,060
after it was revealed
that Mr. Cha repeatedly used

347
00:22:11,143 --> 00:22:14,188
intimidation tactics
while acquiring a small business

348
00:22:14,271 --> 00:22:16,106
for his startup brand launch.

349
00:22:17,149 --> 00:22:18,192
You're going to have to.

350
00:22:18,275 --> 00:22:20,110
This is your first and last chance

351
00:22:20,194 --> 00:22:22,696
to get even a pittance
for that measly company of yours.

352
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:24,823
The price drops by a billion won
every ten seconds.

353
00:22:24,907 --> 00:22:27,326
Even now, thinking about being
extorted and bled dry

354
00:22:27,409 --> 00:22:28,994
by someone young enough to be my son

355
00:22:29,078 --> 00:22:30,663
cuts me to the core.

356
00:22:30,746 --> 00:22:33,457
The spokesperson stressed it is time
for the Fair Trade Commission

357
00:22:33,540 --> 00:22:35,626
to crack down and put an end

358
00:22:35,709 --> 00:22:38,754
to these diabolical acts of preying
on the small businesses

359
00:22:38,837 --> 00:22:41,882
that keep Korea's economy running.

360
00:22:41,966 --> 00:22:45,761
I let you off with money instead
of handcuffs, and this is what I get?

361
00:22:45,844 --> 00:22:47,179
I stole your livelihood?

362
00:22:47,262 --> 00:22:50,474
He must've found out the raw materials
got FDA approval right after the sale,

363
00:22:50,557 --> 00:22:52,351
leaving him feeling bitter.

364
00:22:52,434 --> 00:22:54,520
I'm in the headlines a lot lately.

365
00:22:54,603 --> 00:22:55,604
Any stock impact?

366
00:22:55,688 --> 00:22:57,856
It's plateauing around 87,000 won,

367
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,984
but they haven't
publicly identified you yet.

368
00:23:00,067 --> 00:23:02,820
I'll have the legal team handle it
before it becomes a risk factor.

369
00:23:02,903 --> 00:23:03,821
Don't worry.

370
00:23:03,904 --> 00:23:05,114
No, I should worry.

371
00:23:05,197 --> 00:23:07,199
Without any upward catalysts
before the launch,

372
00:23:07,282 --> 00:23:08,867
even 80,000 won is precarious.

373
00:23:08,951 --> 00:23:11,328
Leave the legal team out of it.
We'll tackle this head-on.

374
00:23:11,412 --> 00:23:13,664
-"Head-on"?
-He's not relying on legalities right now.

375
00:23:13,747 --> 00:23:15,457
He's looking to whip up public sentiment.

376
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:16,917
Then we go eye for an eye.

377
00:23:17,001 --> 00:23:19,545
Forget the law.
We need to rattle his nerves.

378
00:23:19,628 --> 00:23:21,088
Leak it all to the tabloids.

379
00:23:21,171 --> 00:23:23,215
The photos of him gallivanting
around Kangwon Land Casino

380
00:23:23,298 --> 00:23:24,466
after pocketing employee bonuses

381
00:23:24,550 --> 00:23:27,344
and every last piece of evidence
of the cheap raw material swap.

382
00:23:27,428 --> 00:23:30,639
Expose that fake saint
for the fraud he is.

383
00:23:30,723 --> 00:23:32,016
Yes, sir.

384
00:23:32,099 --> 00:23:34,226
RUTHLESS CHAEBOL STEALS
LIVELIHOOD OF SMALL BUSINESSES

385
00:23:35,602 --> 00:23:38,272
I keep them out of prison,
and they stab me in the back.

386
00:23:38,355 --> 00:23:41,066
Nobody knows how to be grateful anymore.

387
00:23:41,692 --> 00:23:42,985
Thank you.

388
00:23:43,068 --> 00:23:45,529
I have met many people here,

389
00:23:45,612 --> 00:23:48,157
but you have been the kindest to me,
and I am most thankful.

390
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,367
That is right. I felt nothing.

391
00:23:51,076 --> 00:23:53,537
It was less thrilling
than hugging a stray mutt.

392
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:55,831
Does she suffer
from multiple personalities?

393
00:23:56,999 --> 00:24:00,544
Hot one minute, cold the next.
Is she playing hard to get or something?

394
00:24:04,965 --> 00:24:07,968
She's actually playing hard to get.

395
00:24:13,474 --> 00:24:15,976
-Manager Gu.
-She took it too far.

396
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,144
-Uncle!
-Manager Gu.

397
00:24:17,227 --> 00:24:18,228
-Uncle.
-Uncle!

398
00:24:18,312 --> 00:24:19,563
-Wake up, Uncle.
-What?

399
00:24:19,646 --> 00:24:21,732
-Uncle, wake up.
-What's up?

400
00:24:21,815 --> 00:24:23,901
You need to deal
with that mess on the roof!

401
00:24:25,819 --> 00:24:28,655
I've told her so many times
to watch the noise!

402
00:24:28,739 --> 00:24:31,200
What the… What is all this?

403
00:24:33,077 --> 00:24:35,204
Rooftop, what in the world is going on…

404
00:24:42,586 --> 00:24:45,839
Hail, boundless life!

405
00:24:47,216 --> 00:24:51,553
Hail, the Great Spirit!

406
00:24:52,179 --> 00:24:53,305
Manager Gu.

407
00:24:53,972 --> 00:24:55,182
Oh my God!

408
00:24:56,266 --> 00:24:57,643
Manager Gu, are you here

409
00:24:57,726 --> 00:24:59,645
to watch the ritual
and grab some free rice cakes?

410
00:24:59,728 --> 00:25:01,980
B-Bloo… B-Blood…

411
00:25:02,064 --> 00:25:04,900
Right. This is not human blood.
It is coagulated ox blood.

412
00:25:04,983 --> 00:25:06,944
Why would you put on
such a terrifying getup?

413
00:25:07,027 --> 00:25:09,113
I'm about to enter the battlefield,

414
00:25:09,196 --> 00:25:12,282
so I thought I would put some on
to ward off evil.

415
00:25:12,366 --> 00:25:14,243
Want some, Manager Gu?

416
00:25:19,832 --> 00:25:21,083
What was today's closing price?

417
00:25:21,166 --> 00:25:22,668
It closed at 82,000 won.

418
00:25:22,751 --> 00:25:24,545
With today's leak making the rounds,

419
00:25:24,628 --> 00:25:27,709
numbers are down slightly
after the deepfake scandal.

420
00:25:27,798 --> 00:25:30,008
Meaning we can't afford any more bad news.

421
00:25:30,592 --> 00:25:32,094
For now, send this out with the photos.

422
00:25:32,177 --> 00:25:34,304
Just to the tabloids,
including financial gossip rags.

423
00:25:34,388 --> 00:25:35,472
Skip mainstream outlets.

424
00:25:35,556 --> 00:25:37,307
Is that necessary when the PR team

425
00:25:37,391 --> 00:25:39,935
already tipped off the deputy managers
about the raw material swap?

426
00:25:40,018 --> 00:25:42,980
What we need isn't a news story.
We just need a good story.

427
00:25:43,063 --> 00:25:45,149
We're throwing bait
for the public to bite,

428
00:25:45,232 --> 00:25:46,483
so we need to spice it up.

429
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:48,193
I should've known.

430
00:25:48,277 --> 00:25:50,904
Your disarmingly cunning tactics

431
00:25:50,988 --> 00:25:52,489
are on another level, sir.

432
00:25:52,573 --> 00:25:54,700
-Speaking of which, Mr. Son.
-Yes, sir.

433
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,375
Never mind.

434
00:26:04,793 --> 00:26:05,961
Yes, sir.

435
00:26:08,714 --> 00:26:10,174
Damn it.

436
00:26:20,976 --> 00:26:22,644
Mr. Son, I have a question.

437
00:26:22,728 --> 00:26:24,980
Yes, sir. Go ahead.

438
00:26:30,527 --> 00:26:31,528
Well…

439
00:26:32,946 --> 00:26:34,573
-Never mind.
-"Never mind"?

440
00:26:48,670 --> 00:26:49,630
Gosh.

441
00:26:50,422 --> 00:26:52,799
Jeez. What is it? Just tell me.

442
00:26:52,883 --> 00:26:55,177
You've been keeping me
in suspense all day.

443
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:57,638
Mr. Son, did you just yell at me?

444
00:26:57,721 --> 00:26:59,181
No, of course not.

445
00:26:59,264 --> 00:27:00,599
I wasn't yelling.

446
00:27:00,682 --> 00:27:03,268
I was just urging you to tell me
so you'd be less stressed.

447
00:27:03,352 --> 00:27:05,520
That there is no need for you
to agonize over it.

448
00:27:05,604 --> 00:27:08,023
It was an earnest plea, sir.

449
00:27:09,483 --> 00:27:11,193
Since you're pushing so hard, Mr. Son,

450
00:27:11,276 --> 00:27:13,654
I'll be frank with you.

451
00:27:14,279 --> 00:27:15,739
Between a man and a woman…

452
00:27:16,823 --> 00:27:18,325
when it comes to the push-and-pull,

453
00:27:18,408 --> 00:27:20,619
how do you gain the upper hand?

454
00:27:20,702 --> 00:27:21,912
"The push-and-pull"?

455
00:27:22,955 --> 00:27:25,958
It's the storyline of some drama
I've been watching when I can't sleep.

456
00:27:26,041 --> 00:27:28,210
I just leave it on to fall asleep to.

457
00:27:29,711 --> 00:27:30,879
Well!

458
00:27:30,963 --> 00:27:33,882
The way I see it, timing is everything
when playing hard to get.

459
00:27:33,966 --> 00:27:36,009
The reality is,
you just have to bombard them.

460
00:27:36,093 --> 00:27:37,594
Give them no time to play games.

461
00:27:37,678 --> 00:27:40,514
Because love
is just another form of warfare.

462
00:27:41,223 --> 00:27:42,933
By bombardment, do you mean

463
00:27:43,016 --> 00:27:45,394
just overwhelming them
with a massive offensive?

464
00:27:45,477 --> 00:27:47,396
In the war of courtship,
losing is winning.

465
00:27:47,479 --> 00:27:49,773
Just say,
"I surrender! I'll die without you!"

466
00:27:49,856 --> 00:27:51,775
When you throw away all your pride,

467
00:27:51,858 --> 00:27:53,986
that's when you truly gain the upper hand.

468
00:27:54,569 --> 00:27:57,155
So what about you?

469
00:27:57,239 --> 00:27:59,032
Have you won every battle
using that method?

470
00:27:59,116 --> 00:28:00,200
I've lost every battle.

471
00:28:00,284 --> 00:28:02,286
Theory is just theory, after all.

472
00:28:06,915 --> 00:28:09,126
-Let's go.
-Right away, sir.

473
00:28:13,380 --> 00:28:16,049
A full-on bombardment
and a massive offensive…

474
00:28:19,011 --> 00:28:22,681
As if you could ever gain the upper hand
with such a cliché strategy.

475
00:28:24,891 --> 00:28:26,560
Isn't there anything else?

476
00:28:26,643 --> 00:28:29,771
No. What don't you like about this one?

477
00:28:29,855 --> 00:28:31,356
It doesn't fit quite right.

478
00:28:33,066 --> 00:28:34,234
It doesn't look sharp.

479
00:28:34,818 --> 00:28:38,113
It's the exact same cut
as your usual custom jackets.

480
00:28:39,781 --> 00:28:41,408
Is it just me?

481
00:28:41,992 --> 00:28:43,452
It just feels cliché.

482
00:29:00,469 --> 00:29:02,554
I am finally entering the battlefield.

483
00:29:08,602 --> 00:29:09,853
GRANDMA

484
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:12,356
Who…

485
00:29:12,981 --> 00:29:14,399
are you?

486
00:29:18,612 --> 00:29:19,571
Seo-ri, it's Grandma.

487
00:29:20,238 --> 00:29:22,824
Are you doing okay up there?

488
00:29:23,533 --> 00:29:24,618
I am fine.

489
00:29:25,869 --> 00:29:27,204
But is everything okay there?

490
00:29:27,287 --> 00:29:28,830
Is anyone causing trouble again?

491
00:29:28,914 --> 00:29:31,583
No, of course not.
You chased them all away.

492
00:29:31,666 --> 00:29:35,879
But since when were you so agile?

493
00:29:35,962 --> 00:29:37,672
Well, I…

494
00:29:38,256 --> 00:29:40,425
I picked up a few things here and there.

495
00:29:41,468 --> 00:29:44,388
If they swarm in again,
call me right away, okay?

496
00:29:44,471 --> 00:29:45,347
Okay, I will.

497
00:29:46,014 --> 00:29:47,015
Gosh, I have customers.

498
00:29:47,099 --> 00:29:48,558
Don't worry about me, okay?

499
00:29:48,642 --> 00:29:50,560
Make sure you eat well.

500
00:29:50,644 --> 00:29:52,479
Okay, I'm hanging up now.

501
00:29:58,151 --> 00:29:59,778
Seo-ri.

502
00:30:00,404 --> 00:30:02,823
How does it feel to be on set?

503
00:30:03,615 --> 00:30:05,826
It must feel really different,
stepping onto the set this time

504
00:30:05,909 --> 00:30:07,661
as Court Lady Kim,

505
00:30:07,744 --> 00:30:09,246
instead of "Palace Attendant 28."

506
00:30:09,329 --> 00:30:12,624
You only scored a role like this
because you have me.

507
00:30:12,707 --> 00:30:15,627
I am not even the Head Court Lady.
Stop making such a fuss.

508
00:30:15,710 --> 00:30:16,795
Not even a single line.

509
00:30:16,878 --> 00:30:18,880
Even without a single line,
you can steal the scene

510
00:30:18,964 --> 00:30:20,966
with just one look, okay?

511
00:30:21,049 --> 00:30:22,426
-Do your best.
-Did you check continuity?

512
00:30:22,509 --> 00:30:24,344
-Yes, confirmed.
-And the CGI?

513
00:30:24,428 --> 00:30:25,929
Gosh. Ms. Hong.

514
00:30:26,012 --> 00:30:29,182
-Director, how have you been?
-You get prettier by the day.

515
00:30:29,266 --> 00:30:31,184
-Who cares about effort?
-You're too sweet.

516
00:30:31,268 --> 00:30:32,644
Results are what matter.

517
00:30:32,727 --> 00:30:33,687
Shin Seo-ri.

518
00:30:35,188 --> 00:30:38,150
You finally got a role, thanks to me.

519
00:30:38,233 --> 00:30:39,609
You should give it your all

520
00:30:39,693 --> 00:30:41,403
and try to hide that you pulled strings.

521
00:30:41,486 --> 00:30:43,238
If you wish for me to do well,

522
00:30:43,321 --> 00:30:45,740
do not hover around me pointlessly.

523
00:30:45,824 --> 00:30:48,994
That face of yours remains
my only irritant in this place.

524
00:30:49,077 --> 00:30:50,829
But remember,
when the cameras are rolling,

525
00:30:50,912 --> 00:30:52,831
I am the Queen,

526
00:30:52,914 --> 00:30:56,001
and you are just a lowly court lady.

527
00:30:56,084 --> 00:30:58,545
Even I can't save you if you can't act.

528
00:30:58,628 --> 00:30:59,838
-Let's go.
-This way.

529
00:31:02,007 --> 00:31:03,091
As if.

530
00:31:03,633 --> 00:31:05,218
Why, that minx…

531
00:31:05,302 --> 00:31:07,012
She is putting on airs

532
00:31:07,095 --> 00:31:09,097
just because she is in the Queen's garb.

533
00:31:09,681 --> 00:31:11,349
What's taking so long?

534
00:31:14,811 --> 00:31:15,979
Oh my God!

535
00:31:16,062 --> 00:31:17,856
Gosh. Oh no…

536
00:31:17,939 --> 00:31:19,024
I'm so sorry.

537
00:31:19,107 --> 00:31:20,734
You should watch where you're going.

538
00:31:21,693 --> 00:31:24,863
I'll pay for the dry cleaning.
No, I'll pay for the suit.

539
00:31:24,946 --> 00:31:27,741
You should find out how much it is
before you offer to pay for it.

540
00:31:27,824 --> 00:31:29,743
I'm a regular here too, so I know.

541
00:31:29,826 --> 00:31:32,037
It's my fault, so I should compensate you.

542
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,997
I'll pass on that offer.

543
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:37,125
I'm not so poor that I need
to beg for free clothes.

544
00:31:37,209 --> 00:31:38,668
Sir.

545
00:31:40,962 --> 00:31:42,714
-Are you okay?
-Wait, what happened…

546
00:31:42,797 --> 00:31:44,883
Please step this way first.

547
00:31:44,966 --> 00:31:46,801
Just get me a fresh one. Same suit.

548
00:31:46,885 --> 00:31:48,303
And send the rest to my house.

549
00:31:48,386 --> 00:31:51,264
But you just got custom suits last week.

550
00:31:51,348 --> 00:31:52,891
Why buy so many jackets again--

551
00:31:52,974 --> 00:31:54,768
Do you starve today
because you ate yesterday?

552
00:31:54,851 --> 00:31:58,021
Don't get me wrong.
I appreciate the business.

553
00:31:58,104 --> 00:32:00,023
This will be my armor.

554
00:32:01,733 --> 00:32:04,569
I've got a battle coming up
that I refuse to lose.

555
00:32:04,653 --> 00:32:06,863
When mating season arrives
in the animal kingdom,

556
00:32:06,947 --> 00:32:09,741
a fierce war of courtship begins.

557
00:32:09,824 --> 00:32:12,911
To seduce a female of their liking,

558
00:32:12,994 --> 00:32:14,955
most males will shower
the females with gifts.

559
00:32:15,038 --> 00:32:19,167
However, some animals seduce females
by showing off their flashy looks.

560
00:32:19,251 --> 00:32:21,253
The male peacock is one of them.

561
00:32:21,962 --> 00:32:24,464
He raises his tail feathers
to show off his beauty.

562
00:32:24,548 --> 00:32:26,758
Just look at him flap those wings.

563
00:32:27,509 --> 00:32:31,596
The peacock flaps its wings desperately
to avoid being left behind.

564
00:32:32,722 --> 00:32:35,809
In this courtship battle
for the female's favor,

565
00:32:35,892 --> 00:32:39,396
will this male emerge victorious?

566
00:32:40,105 --> 00:32:43,900
The results will be revealed
in 60 seconds.

567
00:32:53,243 --> 00:32:55,745
Mi-rae, what's the food truck
serving today?

568
00:32:56,538 --> 00:32:58,873
Darn it. It's spicy stir-fried pork again.

569
00:32:59,416 --> 00:33:01,084
-I like spicy pork.
-Sounds delicious.

570
00:33:03,962 --> 00:33:06,715
Look at Shin Seo-ri beaming and glowing.

571
00:33:06,798 --> 00:33:09,843
You even got a name this time.
"Court Lady Kim So-yun."

572
00:33:09,926 --> 00:33:11,720
Wow…

573
00:33:11,803 --> 00:33:14,431
You are that palace maid.
It has been a while.

574
00:33:14,514 --> 00:33:16,558
I see you have earned the right
to wear a gache.

575
00:33:16,641 --> 00:33:17,851
Oh right.

576
00:33:18,351 --> 00:33:20,854
Yeah, I'm playing a minor court lady too.

577
00:33:21,688 --> 00:33:24,733
I heard you renewed your contract
and landed this role?

578
00:33:24,816 --> 00:33:26,568
How did you ever manage to win Hong over?

579
00:33:26,651 --> 00:33:28,945
She was totally ready
to terminate your contract before.

580
00:33:29,029 --> 00:33:30,196
Why the sudden renewal?

581
00:33:30,280 --> 00:33:32,115
Do not drag up old history.

582
00:33:32,198 --> 00:33:34,284
People ought to live looking ahead.

583
00:33:34,367 --> 00:33:35,285
Excuse me.

584
00:33:38,705 --> 00:33:40,957
She's got this weird aura now.

585
00:33:41,041 --> 00:33:42,000
GONG TAE-WOO'S SURPRISE ROMANCE

586
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:43,043
My poor head.

587
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:45,378
-I'm about to get a cramp.
-Damn it.

588
00:33:45,462 --> 00:33:47,380
Hey, are we shooting Scene 36 today?

589
00:33:47,464 --> 00:33:48,715
Gong Tae-woo.

590
00:33:48,798 --> 00:33:51,593
Do I really have to see
your cheating trending online?

591
00:33:51,676 --> 00:33:54,095
You'd better text back
while I'm still asking nicely.

592
00:33:54,179 --> 00:33:56,723
Ji-hyo, wasn't she
your stand-in last time?

593
00:33:56,806 --> 00:33:57,974
The one who had the meltdown.

594
00:33:58,058 --> 00:33:59,309
Wait, isn't she Shin Seo-ri?

595
00:33:59,392 --> 00:34:01,978
The lead in that old drama, Sonagi.

596
00:34:02,062 --> 00:34:03,104
You're right.

597
00:34:03,188 --> 00:34:05,065
"The Nation's Pebble, Shin Seo-ri."

598
00:34:05,148 --> 00:34:07,275
Ji-hyo, you made your acting debut
in that drama too.

599
00:34:07,359 --> 00:34:09,152
What? Ji-hyo was in that too?

600
00:34:09,235 --> 00:34:11,988
Yeah, she was
the class president in another class.

601
00:34:12,072 --> 00:34:14,115
The annoying girl who always
bullied the female lead--

602
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:15,158
That's ancient history!

603
00:34:15,992 --> 00:34:18,745
Have you forgotten the part
where her career tanked six months later

604
00:34:18,828 --> 00:34:19,788
because she can't act?

605
00:34:19,871 --> 00:34:21,039
Damn it.

606
00:34:21,581 --> 00:34:24,626
What the hell is she doing
with the assistant director anyway?

607
00:34:24,709 --> 00:34:27,337
Listen here.
Those two hanging around that minx.

608
00:34:27,420 --> 00:34:29,422
Are they supposed to be
Consorts Su-gui and So-yong?

609
00:34:29,506 --> 00:34:30,965
Excuse me? "Minx"?

610
00:34:31,591 --> 00:34:32,509
I mean Yoon Ji-hyo.

611
00:34:32,592 --> 00:34:35,428
I believe that minx is playing
the role of the Queen.

612
00:34:35,512 --> 00:34:37,305
Why does the Queen's hair look like that?

613
00:34:37,389 --> 00:34:40,016
And why are those underlings
wearing gaches en masse?

614
00:34:40,100 --> 00:34:42,143
-What about it?
-During King Anjong's reign,

615
00:34:42,227 --> 00:34:43,895
the ban on gaches was issued.

616
00:34:43,978 --> 00:34:44,854
So I ask you

617
00:34:44,938 --> 00:34:47,982
because those Inner Court minions
are all proudly wearing their gaches.

618
00:34:48,066 --> 00:34:48,983
Change them at once.

619
00:34:49,609 --> 00:34:52,112
I mean, who are you to demand
we make changes?

620
00:34:52,195 --> 00:34:53,279
I mean…

621
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:57,367
What are you doing here?
I told you to get the cinematographer.

622
00:34:57,450 --> 00:34:59,077
Well, this woman

623
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,787
was spouting nonsense about the gaches.

624
00:35:00,870 --> 00:35:02,539
How dare you! "Nonsense"?

625
00:35:02,622 --> 00:35:06,543
Even if moral standards have hit
rock bottom in Hell Joseon,

626
00:35:06,626 --> 00:35:08,503
should we not at least strive
for historical accuracy?

627
00:35:08,586 --> 00:35:09,671
Excuse me.

628
00:35:09,754 --> 00:35:11,965
You were the stand-in
for Royal Consort Jang last time, right?

629
00:35:12,048 --> 00:35:13,800
"Jang"? I am of the Kang clan!

630
00:35:13,883 --> 00:35:15,385
Look at that projection.

631
00:35:15,468 --> 00:35:16,553
Great commanding tone.

632
00:35:16,636 --> 00:35:18,304
Thanks to that commanding tone,

633
00:35:18,388 --> 00:35:20,140
our drama shorts got a lot of buzz.

634
00:35:20,223 --> 00:35:22,851
But that one viral moment has got you
way too committed to the bit.

635
00:35:22,934 --> 00:35:25,353
You're in too deep. You can't do that.

636
00:35:25,437 --> 00:35:26,980
Are you the chief here?

637
00:35:27,063 --> 00:35:28,565
Right, I'm the chief…

638
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:30,066
"Chief"?

639
00:35:30,150 --> 00:35:32,318
I have been utterly unable
to reason with this dunce.

640
00:35:32,402 --> 00:35:34,362
Your presence is most welcome.

641
00:35:34,446 --> 00:35:37,365
Let us go somewhere quiet
and have a frank discussion.

642
00:35:38,199 --> 00:35:41,161
Director, what's going on?

643
00:35:41,244 --> 00:35:43,705
Ji-hyo. She's an actor
from your agency, right?

644
00:35:44,330 --> 00:35:46,499
Where is Ms. Hong? Go get Ms. Hong.

645
00:35:46,583 --> 00:35:48,835
She needs to keep her actors in check.
This is unacceptable.

646
00:35:48,918 --> 00:35:52,505
Oh my, did Seo-ri already make
some sort of mistake?

647
00:35:52,589 --> 00:35:53,673
I'm so sorry.

648
00:35:53,757 --> 00:35:55,467
I know we're from the same agency,

649
00:35:55,550 --> 00:35:58,470
but I did warn them
against pulling strings for her.

650
00:35:58,553 --> 00:36:00,847
I'm mortified as the lead of this drama.

651
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:02,140
As if.

652
00:36:02,223 --> 00:36:03,308
This is why

653
00:36:03,391 --> 00:36:05,560
I say you can't fix up
an old, washed-up rookie.

654
00:36:05,643 --> 00:36:07,479
Didn't I, you dunce?
You cast her, didn't you?

655
00:36:07,562 --> 00:36:08,772
She must be a favor hire.

656
00:36:08,855 --> 00:36:10,690
Jeez. No wonder.

657
00:36:11,274 --> 00:36:13,985
These wretches dare to publicly shame me

658
00:36:14,068 --> 00:36:16,488
to my very face.

659
00:36:18,281 --> 00:36:20,366
Listen, since Ji-hyo
is speaking up for you,

660
00:36:20,450 --> 00:36:21,618
I'll let it slide this once.

661
00:36:21,701 --> 00:36:23,369
But there won't be a second time.

662
00:36:23,453 --> 00:36:24,704
You should offer her a deep bow.

663
00:36:24,788 --> 00:36:26,498
-What?
-No need.

664
00:36:26,581 --> 00:36:28,833
It's fine, Director. Please calm down.

665
00:36:28,917 --> 00:36:31,753
The crew is working so hard.

666
00:36:31,836 --> 00:36:35,173
Let me treat everyone to iced Americanos
to celebrate the start of Season 2.

667
00:36:35,256 --> 00:36:36,758
Let's get back to it.

668
00:36:36,841 --> 00:36:38,968
-Look here, Chief.
-She's not a favor hire.

669
00:36:39,052 --> 00:36:42,055
-"Chief"? Did she really call me that?
-Come on, Director.

670
00:36:43,139 --> 00:36:45,225
What's her name again? Seo-ri?

671
00:36:53,942 --> 00:36:56,236
Cut! Okay, next scene!

672
00:37:00,281 --> 00:37:01,699
Great work, everyone.

673
00:37:03,409 --> 00:37:05,954
Look at that minx asserting her dominion

674
00:37:06,037 --> 00:37:07,455
and marking her territory.

675
00:37:09,332 --> 00:37:10,708
It is both infuriating and grating.

676
00:37:10,792 --> 00:37:13,169
Swiftly rising to distinction
is my only option.

677
00:37:14,003 --> 00:37:15,713
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

678
00:37:15,797 --> 00:37:17,632
-Thanks for the latte.
-Thank you.

679
00:37:17,715 --> 00:37:20,093
-Good luck, Seo-ri.
-Thanks for the drink.

680
00:37:20,176 --> 00:37:21,761
-Thanks for the drink.
-Thank you.

681
00:37:21,845 --> 00:37:23,847
-Thank you.
-Thanks for the treat.

682
00:37:24,597 --> 00:37:25,515
What the…

683
00:37:26,140 --> 00:37:28,601
Why are they suddenly being so nice?

684
00:37:36,776 --> 00:37:40,071
The number you have dialed is unavailable.
You will be transferred to voicemail…

685
00:37:40,154 --> 00:37:42,031
Now he's blocked me?

686
00:37:42,574 --> 00:37:44,701
That scumbag. Damn it.

687
00:37:47,412 --> 00:37:48,830
Go get me an iced Americano.

688
00:37:48,913 --> 00:37:50,415
-Overflowing with ice.
-Okay.

689
00:37:50,498 --> 00:37:52,834
Yes, sure. Thank you.

690
00:37:52,917 --> 00:37:54,878
Hey, the delivery is going to be delayed

691
00:37:54,961 --> 00:37:56,421
because it's lunchtime.

692
00:37:57,005 --> 00:37:58,923
-Isn't that what you ordered?
-What?

693
00:37:59,007 --> 00:38:00,508
Someone else sent a coffee truck?

694
00:38:00,592 --> 00:38:03,386
I'll cancel our order right away.

695
00:38:03,970 --> 00:38:05,013
Really?

696
00:38:05,096 --> 00:38:07,682
The lead should kick it off.
Who could be this thoughtless?

697
00:38:09,350 --> 00:38:10,935
Wait. Hold on a second.

698
00:38:12,228 --> 00:38:14,939
"Courtesy of Shin Seo-ri,
the acting virtuoso"?

699
00:38:15,023 --> 00:38:15,899
Ji-hyo.

700
00:38:17,817 --> 00:38:20,236
Did Shin Seo-ri send a coffee truck?

701
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:22,322
COURTESY OF SHIN SEO-RI
THE ACTING VIRTUOSO

702
00:38:22,739 --> 00:38:23,698
SHIN SEO-RI'S QUEENDOM OF BEAUTY

703
00:38:28,536 --> 00:38:30,705
-This is me. Right here.
-Seo-ri, you look beautiful.

704
00:38:30,788 --> 00:38:32,248
Please look over here.

705
00:38:32,332 --> 00:38:34,584
You're so pretty. I'm a fan.

706
00:38:38,963 --> 00:38:40,340
-Could I get a picture?
-Sure.

707
00:38:44,844 --> 00:38:45,803
Thank you.

708
00:38:45,887 --> 00:38:48,222
Thank you, Seo-ri. Thanks for the treat.

709
00:38:48,848 --> 00:38:51,768
-Thanks for the treat.
-Thank you, everyone.

710
00:38:53,019 --> 00:38:54,312
In my entire life,

711
00:38:54,395 --> 00:38:57,815
I have never before received
gratitude from such a horde at once.

712
00:38:57,899 --> 00:39:00,526
It is a hundred times better
than being treated like dirt.

713
00:39:00,610 --> 00:39:02,153
Seo-ri, you're so pretty.

714
00:39:03,071 --> 00:39:04,447
I am Shin Seo-ri.

715
00:39:04,989 --> 00:39:06,240
I am the Shin Seo-ri.

716
00:39:08,076 --> 00:39:09,786
Now, smile.

717
00:39:12,330 --> 00:39:14,040
How does it feel, Shin Seo-ri?

718
00:39:16,584 --> 00:39:18,753
Are you finally feeling
that tsunami of emotion?

719
00:39:18,836 --> 00:39:19,921
Cha Se-gye?

720
00:39:20,838 --> 00:39:21,965
Don't say my name out loud.

721
00:39:22,048 --> 00:39:23,091
Wait…

722
00:39:24,342 --> 00:39:26,219
Was this all your doing, Cha Se-gye?

723
00:39:26,302 --> 00:39:28,262
Seriously? I just told you
to stop saying my name.

724
00:39:28,346 --> 00:39:29,305
You scoundrel.

725
00:39:29,389 --> 00:39:30,390
Ms. Hong.

726
00:39:30,473 --> 00:39:33,226
You paired Shin Seo-ri up with me
without saying anything,

727
00:39:33,309 --> 00:39:35,019
and now you're even sending coffee trucks?

728
00:39:35,103 --> 00:39:37,772
Have you ever seen me waste my money?

729
00:39:37,855 --> 00:39:39,565
There's a proper order to everything.

730
00:39:39,649 --> 00:39:42,235
Why would I get one for her first?

731
00:39:42,318 --> 00:39:46,489
Hold on. So it really wasn't you?

732
00:39:46,572 --> 00:39:47,782
-No.
-Then,

733
00:39:47,865 --> 00:39:50,034
who the hell wasted their money on that?

734
00:39:50,118 --> 00:39:52,870
Maybe a fan sent it.

735
00:39:52,954 --> 00:39:54,831
Since when does she have fans?

736
00:39:58,501 --> 00:39:59,419
Damn it.

737
00:40:00,753 --> 00:40:02,046
I mean…

738
00:40:04,757 --> 00:40:06,092
What are you plotting now?

739
00:40:06,175 --> 00:40:08,678
What scheme are you hatching
that requires such bribery?

740
00:40:10,513 --> 00:40:12,015
I suppose you could call it a bribe.

741
00:40:12,098 --> 00:40:13,182
There is an ulterior motive.

742
00:40:13,266 --> 00:40:14,642
"Ulterior motive"?

743
00:40:14,726 --> 00:40:16,894
Now you are finally showing
your true colors.

744
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:19,939
You are not a fan or an ally,
yet you pretended to care.

745
00:40:20,023 --> 00:40:21,941
What is your ulterior motive?

746
00:40:28,114 --> 00:40:30,783
As of today,
I'm officially setting this as my target.

747
00:40:31,784 --> 00:40:33,161
My heart.

748
00:40:33,745 --> 00:40:35,246
What are you going to do to it?

749
00:40:35,329 --> 00:40:37,373
Yeah. I'm going to steal your heart.

750
00:40:38,875 --> 00:40:39,959
You said you felt nothing.

751
00:40:40,043 --> 00:40:41,669
That I moved you less than a stray mutt.

752
00:40:41,753 --> 00:40:43,796
I haven't slept for days after that.

753
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:44,964
It got to me.

754
00:40:45,048 --> 00:40:48,509
Whether you sleep or do handstands,
what does that have to do with me?

755
00:40:48,593 --> 00:40:50,136
Look at you, acting tough again.

756
00:40:50,219 --> 00:40:53,139
The thing is,
I realized I overlooked something.

757
00:40:53,723 --> 00:40:54,640
And what is that?

758
00:40:54,724 --> 00:40:57,894
That a woman like you, Shin Seo-ri,
is far from innocent.

759
00:40:59,020 --> 00:41:01,272
Are you saying I am dirty and vulgar?

760
00:41:01,355 --> 00:41:02,607
You're a skilled liar.

761
00:41:03,232 --> 00:41:05,777
You'll use any means necessary
to achieve your goals.

762
00:41:05,860 --> 00:41:07,862
In short, you're a dangerous woman.

763
00:41:09,405 --> 00:41:11,157
So are you going to be petty now

764
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:13,659
and suggest we cancel our contract?

765
00:41:13,743 --> 00:41:15,286
But the thing is,

766
00:41:15,369 --> 00:41:17,038
I've never been one to lose.

767
00:41:17,121 --> 00:41:19,457
So I'm confident
I won't lose this time either.

768
00:41:21,084 --> 00:41:22,293
Maybe not?

769
00:41:22,376 --> 00:41:24,087
Is he looking for a fight?

770
00:41:25,421 --> 00:41:27,423
-Is this retaliation?
-No, it's a surrender.

771
00:41:28,883 --> 00:41:31,761
They say in love and war,
sometimes losing is winning.

772
00:41:34,055 --> 00:41:36,766
What is with this intense stare?

773
00:41:36,849 --> 00:41:39,143
Look, I admit I skipped
the romantic gestures

774
00:41:39,227 --> 00:41:40,895
and acted a bit rashly.

775
00:41:41,729 --> 00:41:45,399
So let's wipe the slate clean

776
00:41:45,483 --> 00:41:46,526
and start over.

777
00:41:46,609 --> 00:41:49,403
What is with this duplicity?

778
00:41:49,487 --> 00:41:51,447
Cold and ruthless to the core,

779
00:41:51,531 --> 00:41:53,741
yet those eyes are nothing but sincere.

780
00:41:54,367 --> 00:41:55,576
Could he be…

781
00:41:56,577 --> 00:42:00,373
Do you… truly harbor affection for me?

782
00:42:00,998 --> 00:42:01,874
I do.

783
00:42:08,714 --> 00:42:12,718
Why is this fool
charging in headfirst like this?

784
00:42:23,938 --> 00:42:26,190
I get it. You're a woman,

785
00:42:26,274 --> 00:42:28,734
so accepting right away
would hurt your pride.

786
00:42:29,902 --> 00:42:31,988
I'll give you a day to protect your ego.

787
00:42:32,071 --> 00:42:33,531
No need.

788
00:42:33,614 --> 00:42:34,782
Here is my definitive answer.

789
00:42:36,993 --> 00:42:38,953
It has never changed,
and I guarantee it never will.

790
00:42:39,036 --> 00:42:40,079
Cha Se-gye.

791
00:42:40,163 --> 00:42:41,706
I harbor

792
00:42:41,789 --> 00:42:42,957
no affection for you.

793
00:42:44,125 --> 00:42:46,627
Not now, not ever, until the end of time.

794
00:42:56,095 --> 00:42:57,180
Oh my.

795
00:43:01,601 --> 00:43:03,728
That wicked degenerate.

796
00:43:03,811 --> 00:43:05,980
Launching a surprise attack
in close combat.

797
00:43:07,398 --> 00:43:08,816
I am a Buddhist nun.

798
00:43:08,900 --> 00:43:10,401
A Buddhist nun with long hair.

799
00:43:25,208 --> 00:43:26,292
Hey, Shin Seo-ri.

800
00:43:26,959 --> 00:43:29,003
You take this.
The smell is giving me a headache.

801
00:43:29,086 --> 00:43:30,129
You…

802
00:43:32,506 --> 00:43:33,549
Did you buy flowers too?

803
00:43:33,633 --> 00:43:35,426
Don't read into it. It's annoying.

804
00:43:47,188 --> 00:43:48,105
What's that about?

805
00:43:51,609 --> 00:43:53,486
That's a supercar.

806
00:43:54,487 --> 00:43:56,697
Shin Seo-ri, that loser, has a boyfriend?

807
00:44:11,003 --> 00:44:12,546
You dare reject me?

808
00:44:12,630 --> 00:44:14,966
Not just once, but twice?

809
00:44:20,137 --> 00:44:22,139
CHIEF OF STAFF SON JAE-HAN

810
00:44:22,473 --> 00:44:23,933
Sir, you're on your way, right?

811
00:44:24,016 --> 00:44:26,269
Today is the dinner
at the Chairman's estate.

812
00:44:26,352 --> 00:44:28,145
-Did you perhaps forget--
-Do you have any idea

813
00:44:28,229 --> 00:44:31,315
the humiliation I just suffered
because of you, Mr. Son?

814
00:44:31,399 --> 00:44:32,942
Wait, what did I do--

815
00:44:33,025 --> 00:44:35,820
That's on me for asking
a cat-cuddling old bachelor.

816
00:44:53,087 --> 00:44:54,338
Damn it.

817
00:44:54,422 --> 00:44:57,091
Oh my, I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

818
00:44:57,758 --> 00:45:00,553
-It's you, right?
-What?

819
00:45:01,721 --> 00:45:03,556
Earlier at the shop.

820
00:45:04,265 --> 00:45:05,141
Don't you remember?

821
00:45:05,224 --> 00:45:07,184
Shop? What shop?

822
00:45:07,268 --> 00:45:08,144
Have we met?

823
00:45:08,227 --> 00:45:09,687
The coffee at the tailor shop.

824
00:45:09,770 --> 00:45:11,522
I spilled coffee on you.

825
00:45:11,605 --> 00:45:13,065
Right, that coffee.

826
00:45:14,025 --> 00:45:16,402
You seem to be quite accident-prone.

827
00:45:17,028 --> 00:45:19,739
I don't think my face is that forgettable.

828
00:45:22,366 --> 00:45:24,327
Don't say no a second time. Call me.

829
00:45:24,410 --> 00:45:27,246
Aftereffects of a car accident
are what get you.

830
00:45:31,917 --> 00:45:34,545
-"Trinice"?
-It's my company.

831
00:45:34,628 --> 00:45:37,715
I've got enough money not to hit
someone's car and just drive off,

832
00:45:37,798 --> 00:45:40,676
so make sure to bill me
for your treatment.

833
00:45:53,189 --> 00:45:55,441
An epic clash
of relentlessly stubborn titans.

834
00:45:55,524 --> 00:45:58,778
Is this the age-old battle
of spear versus shield?

835
00:45:58,861 --> 00:46:01,489
Weren't you the one who told me
to stop going on blind dates?

836
00:46:01,572 --> 00:46:05,701
I've already struck out in that world
and been blacklisted there.

837
00:46:05,785 --> 00:46:07,411
You may have struck out domestically,

838
00:46:07,495 --> 00:46:10,373
but the overseas market
remains an untapped goldmine.

839
00:46:10,456 --> 00:46:12,750
Counter twisted logic
by twisting your own.

840
00:46:12,833 --> 00:46:14,126
Does scrap metal turn into silver

841
00:46:14,210 --> 00:46:16,629
just by crossing an ocean, Grandfather?

842
00:46:16,712 --> 00:46:19,173
Stop complaining and make time this week.

843
00:46:19,256 --> 00:46:21,675
I don't even mind
if she can't speak Korean well.

844
00:46:22,468 --> 00:46:23,552
Utilize false reasoning

845
00:46:23,636 --> 00:46:26,347
and distortion to force
the desired conclusion.

846
00:46:28,140 --> 00:46:30,017
I really don't have the time.

847
00:46:35,940 --> 00:46:38,526
Grandfather, are you trying
to pull a ruse?

848
00:46:41,278 --> 00:46:43,280
I almost fell for it.

849
00:46:45,282 --> 00:46:46,617
Sharp-eyed devil.

850
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:49,745
You were so hopeless at blind dates.

851
00:46:49,829 --> 00:46:52,915
I figured you were more
of an organic meeting type.

852
00:46:52,998 --> 00:46:54,291
Was that so terrible of me?

853
00:46:54,375 --> 00:46:55,751
"Organic." How hip.

854
00:46:55,835 --> 00:46:58,212
If she's willing to play along
with this ridiculous act,

855
00:46:58,295 --> 00:46:59,547
it's obvious what she's like.

856
00:46:59,630 --> 00:47:01,298
Either naive or stupid.

857
00:47:01,382 --> 00:47:03,759
She's a smart young lady
who's perfect for you.

858
00:47:03,843 --> 00:47:05,594
That's why I changed my mind.

859
00:47:05,678 --> 00:47:07,346
You must have met her first.

860
00:47:07,430 --> 00:47:09,098
If she's that great, you should marry her.

861
00:47:09,181 --> 00:47:10,766
What? You rotten punk!

862
00:47:10,850 --> 00:47:13,310
When you're outmatched,
go for the jugular.

863
00:47:13,394 --> 00:47:15,062
A foolproof strategy for victory.

864
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,209
I do.

865
00:47:41,380 --> 00:47:42,548
Jeez.

866
00:47:49,472 --> 00:47:53,601
Did he really think some common flowers
would sway me in the slightest?

867
00:47:55,186 --> 00:47:57,104
My welfare is my first priority.

868
00:47:57,188 --> 00:47:58,689
And my second.

869
00:48:00,107 --> 00:48:02,776
In this life,
I will be sure to guard my heart

870
00:48:03,944 --> 00:48:06,030
and live out my days to the fullest.

871
00:48:18,751 --> 00:48:20,169
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

872
00:48:23,547 --> 00:48:25,508
Your Highness, what brings you here?

873
00:48:25,591 --> 00:48:27,134
These are my secret quarters.

874
00:48:27,218 --> 00:48:28,761
What are you doing here?

875
00:48:30,012 --> 00:48:31,180
I was just…

876
00:48:40,648 --> 00:48:41,857
What are you burying?

877
00:48:42,483 --> 00:48:44,735
Did you bury a stolen trinket?

878
00:48:46,028 --> 00:48:48,322
I did not steal anything.

879
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:51,367
Do you take me for some petty thief?

880
00:48:51,909 --> 00:48:54,245
There, the spark is back in your eyes.

881
00:48:54,328 --> 00:48:56,413
Do not sulk like some mutt
caught in the rain.

882
00:48:56,497 --> 00:48:58,624
You are only yourself when you are feisty.

883
00:48:59,667 --> 00:49:01,377
Speaking of,

884
00:49:01,460 --> 00:49:04,171
where did that mutt go?

885
00:49:07,716 --> 00:49:09,635
Did you chase it away?

886
00:49:18,769 --> 00:49:21,522
Or… is it dead?

887
00:49:25,568 --> 00:49:27,278
It died.

888
00:49:29,863 --> 00:49:31,991
I killed it.

889
00:49:35,286 --> 00:49:36,662
That cannot be true.

890
00:49:36,745 --> 00:49:38,372
If you had indeed killed it,

891
00:49:38,455 --> 00:49:41,792
you would not be looking so distraught,
making a grave for it.

892
00:49:52,052 --> 00:49:53,929
Let us at least pray

893
00:49:54,013 --> 00:49:56,140
for this nameless dog's soul.

894
00:49:57,558 --> 00:49:59,560
So that it may find peace
in the afterlife.

895
00:50:02,896 --> 00:50:03,939
May you

896
00:50:04,982 --> 00:50:08,777
be reborn as a human in your next life
and live out your days to the fullest.

897
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:18,454
May you live out your days to the fullest.

898
00:51:21,517 --> 00:51:23,477
Why did he have to give me these?

899
00:51:25,979 --> 00:51:29,233
But they are still living things.
I cannot just throw them away.

900
00:51:29,316 --> 00:51:31,026
It'd be a waste to toss out flowers.

901
00:51:31,110 --> 00:51:32,361
Someone must've asked her out.

902
00:51:32,444 --> 00:51:34,613
Did Unit 204 give it to you?

903
00:51:34,697 --> 00:51:35,572
Be quiet.

904
00:51:35,656 --> 00:51:37,408
Enough chattering.
Hang your laundry and go.

905
00:51:38,450 --> 00:51:40,369
Jeez. What's with the attitude?

906
00:51:43,080 --> 00:51:44,748
Did you watch
The Women's Kingdom yesterday?

907
00:51:44,832 --> 00:51:47,292
I can't believe Season 2 started.

908
00:51:47,376 --> 00:51:48,794
Yoon Ji-hyo got even prettier.

909
00:51:48,877 --> 00:51:51,588
-Her skin is flawless.
-She must spend a fortune on it.

910
00:51:51,672 --> 00:51:53,966
That minx's glowing skin

911
00:51:54,049 --> 00:51:55,718
is just caked-on makeup.

912
00:51:56,385 --> 00:51:58,762
What the… You tell us
to be quiet, then chime in?

913
00:51:58,846 --> 00:52:00,514
She's just dissing her out of jealousy.

914
00:52:00,597 --> 00:52:01,682
As if she's ever seen her.

915
00:52:01,765 --> 00:52:03,809
Of course I have. I saw her yesterday.

916
00:52:03,892 --> 00:52:04,935
Where?

917
00:52:05,561 --> 00:52:08,063
Probably at her part-time gig.

918
00:52:08,147 --> 00:52:09,815
Rooftop is an actor too. A wannabe.

919
00:52:09,898 --> 00:52:12,735
-Stop lying.
-It's true. She goes to film sets.

920
00:52:12,818 --> 00:52:14,361
You think just anyone can be an actor?

921
00:52:14,445 --> 00:52:15,696
Those brats.

922
00:52:15,779 --> 00:52:18,949
I give them my yard for their laundry
and get zero gratitude.

923
00:52:19,825 --> 00:52:20,826
Damn it.

924
00:52:22,953 --> 00:52:26,039
This is why you should never
carelessly let someone in.

925
00:52:33,380 --> 00:52:34,673
I'll be sending the schedule

926
00:52:34,757 --> 00:52:37,259
for the Jeju Island shoot in two days,
so pack your bags.

927
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:40,929
Ji-hyo is on vacation, so I'll let you use
her van and road manager for now.

928
00:52:41,013 --> 00:52:42,097
Take advantage of that.

929
00:52:42,181 --> 00:52:44,641
I refuse anything that belongs
to that minx.

930
00:52:44,725 --> 00:52:47,352
I shall carefully handpick my own person,

931
00:52:47,436 --> 00:52:48,729
so be aware.

932
00:52:53,942 --> 00:52:55,360
Can't sleep lately?

933
00:52:55,444 --> 00:52:59,072
Every time I lie down,
I get so mad that I can't fall asleep.

934
00:52:59,156 --> 00:53:01,366
Lying in bed and suddenly cringing
at the past is normal.

935
00:53:01,450 --> 00:53:03,076
Turn off your brain. Maybe meditate.

936
00:53:03,160 --> 00:53:04,953
How can I turn it off?

937
00:53:05,037 --> 00:53:06,622
I've never been so insulted in my life.

938
00:53:06,705 --> 00:53:08,040
Yeah, the news comments are nuts,

939
00:53:08,123 --> 00:53:10,042
cursing you out
and calling you a corporate raider.

940
00:53:10,125 --> 00:53:13,295
I can't just let this go.
It's too humiliating.

941
00:53:15,297 --> 00:53:16,256
I need revenge.

942
00:53:17,508 --> 00:53:19,259
"Revenge"?

943
00:53:19,802 --> 00:53:22,054
A fresh scandal always drowns out
the last one.

944
00:53:22,137 --> 00:53:24,890
Just be patient.
Time will solve everything.

945
00:53:24,973 --> 00:53:26,517
"Fresh scandal"?

946
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:29,686
Yeah.

947
00:53:30,521 --> 00:53:32,397
That's a good way to bury it.

948
00:53:33,065 --> 00:53:34,733
Thanks for the session today.

949
00:53:34,817 --> 00:53:36,735
You've become a real miracle worker.

950
00:53:37,736 --> 00:53:39,154
Hey, don't forget your meds!

951
00:53:42,616 --> 00:53:45,744
Nurse Kim, could you take this
to Mr. Cha Se-gye?

952
00:53:45,828 --> 00:53:47,579
Sure, give it to me.

953
00:53:49,873 --> 00:53:51,124
Mr. Son.

954
00:53:51,208 --> 00:53:52,501
Call Grandfather.

955
00:53:53,043 --> 00:53:55,337
Tell him I'll go on that blind date
as soon as possible.

956
00:53:55,420 --> 00:53:57,840
Mr. Cha Se-gye, your medication is ready.

957
00:54:00,384 --> 00:54:03,011
No, just stop talking and do it now.

958
00:54:03,095 --> 00:54:04,096
HANBIT MENTAL HEALTH CLINIC

959
00:54:07,349 --> 00:54:09,476
DELIVERY COMPLETED

960
00:54:17,818 --> 00:54:20,195
"In the Anglo-American legal system,

961
00:54:20,737 --> 00:54:24,783
police are formed as an organization
granted autonomous authority by citizens…"

962
00:54:24,867 --> 00:54:25,784
Is that good?

963
00:54:25,868 --> 00:54:27,077
Jesus!

964
00:54:27,870 --> 00:54:30,914
Make some noise when you walk.
You're not a ghost.

965
00:54:38,088 --> 00:54:40,716
Your physique may be lacking,

966
00:54:40,799 --> 00:54:42,885
but you survive on noodles day after day

967
00:54:42,968 --> 00:54:45,345
and remain a penny-pincher.

968
00:54:45,429 --> 00:54:47,306
Your survival skills are top-notch.

969
00:54:50,434 --> 00:54:51,310
What's up?

970
00:54:52,644 --> 00:54:56,106
And despite all my scolding,
you still talk back to me.

971
00:54:56,732 --> 00:54:58,609
You are more tenacious than you look.

972
00:55:00,569 --> 00:55:03,488
Will you place yourself in my service?

973
00:55:03,572 --> 00:55:04,740
What are you talking about?

974
00:55:04,823 --> 00:55:05,949
I shall

975
00:55:06,033 --> 00:55:08,660
personally appoint you as my "nodo."

976
00:55:08,744 --> 00:55:10,495
"Nodo"? What's that?

977
00:55:10,579 --> 00:55:12,539
"No" as in "toil." "Do" as in "guide."

978
00:55:12,623 --> 00:55:13,999
"To guide through toil."

979
00:55:14,082 --> 00:55:16,251
Have you never heard of a "nodo" manager?

980
00:55:16,335 --> 00:55:17,377
"Nodo"?

981
00:55:19,922 --> 00:55:21,089
I see.

982
00:55:21,173 --> 00:55:23,425
You mean "road manager"?

983
00:55:25,636 --> 00:55:27,262
You think I've been working part-time gigs

984
00:55:27,346 --> 00:55:29,139
day and night just to become your driver?

985
00:55:29,222 --> 00:55:30,432
I'll have you know,

986
00:55:30,515 --> 00:55:33,018
I graduated
from a four-year university in Seoul.

987
00:55:33,101 --> 00:55:36,521
So you even possess some knowledge.
You are a perfect fit.

988
00:55:36,605 --> 00:55:39,107
My standards for choosing subordinates
are quite strict,

989
00:55:39,191 --> 00:55:41,401
but no matter how I look at it,

990
00:55:41,485 --> 00:55:42,903
there is no talent quite like you.

991
00:55:42,986 --> 00:55:44,696
Are you even listening to me?

992
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,031
Even if I'm desperate for money,

993
00:55:46,114 --> 00:55:48,659
I'd never be crazy enough to work for you.

994
00:55:48,742 --> 00:55:50,285
How much would satisfy you?

995
00:55:50,369 --> 00:55:51,954
I will pay whatever you ask.

996
00:55:52,037 --> 00:55:54,247
Pay whatever I ask?
You live in a rooftop room.

997
00:55:54,331 --> 00:55:55,832
Three times your minimum wage.

998
00:55:57,042 --> 00:55:59,169
Would three times satisfy you?

999
00:56:02,005 --> 00:56:04,091
You think you can just buy me with money?

1000
00:56:04,174 --> 00:56:05,342
I won't do it! No way!

1001
00:56:05,425 --> 00:56:06,426
Damn it.

1002
00:56:06,927 --> 00:56:08,637
I screwed up. Royally screwed up.

1003
00:56:09,388 --> 00:56:10,931
Damn my need for money.

1004
00:56:11,014 --> 00:56:13,684
She offered triple the pay.
How could I refuse that?

1005
00:56:13,767 --> 00:56:16,812
What are you doing? Move yourself quickly!

1006
00:56:18,063 --> 00:56:19,773
Have you never been to Jeju?

1007
00:56:19,856 --> 00:56:21,149
Why are you so dressed up?

1008
00:56:21,233 --> 00:56:22,985
And what's with the weird glasses?

1009
00:56:23,068 --> 00:56:24,569
As a celebrity,

1010
00:56:24,653 --> 00:56:28,115
one must never let one's guard down,
even at departure.

1011
00:56:28,657 --> 00:56:30,450
Are the reporters not here yet?

1012
00:56:31,118 --> 00:56:32,119
"Departure"?

1013
00:56:32,202 --> 00:56:34,746
By the way, I saw online
that the CEO of the company

1014
00:56:34,830 --> 00:56:36,456
you're shooting the commercial for

1015
00:56:36,540 --> 00:56:39,459
is getting a ton of hate for being
morally corrupt and controversial.

1016
00:56:39,543 --> 00:56:41,420
-You sure about this?
-What does it matter?

1017
00:56:41,503 --> 00:56:43,213
As long as we are making money.

1018
00:56:43,755 --> 00:56:46,967
Then again, that would be the pot
calling the kettle black. Who's to judge?

1019
00:56:47,050 --> 00:56:48,176
Why, you…

1020
00:56:50,429 --> 00:56:54,016
There's absolutely no need for the CEO
to be there for a campaign shoot.

1021
00:56:54,683 --> 00:56:57,728
Out of all our marketing strategies,
isn't this ad the top priority right now?

1022
00:56:57,811 --> 00:57:01,314
The advertiser should be there on set,
overseeing things directly.

1023
00:57:03,358 --> 00:57:06,069
I was hoping to sneak in
some long-overdue PTO on this work trip.

1024
00:57:06,153 --> 00:57:07,195
Guess not.

1025
00:57:09,197 --> 00:57:11,783
Welcome aboard. Have a pleasant flight.

1026
00:57:12,409 --> 00:57:13,785
Welcome aboard.

1027
00:57:15,620 --> 00:57:17,622
If you live long enough,
you really do see it all.

1028
00:57:17,706 --> 00:57:20,625
A marvel to fly through the skies
while still very much alive.

1029
00:57:22,169 --> 00:57:23,628
This will do.

1030
00:57:25,881 --> 00:57:27,758
The seats are so plush.

1031
00:57:27,841 --> 00:57:29,968
I can sleep with both legs stretched out.

1032
00:57:30,594 --> 00:57:32,763
Why do you walk so fast?

1033
00:57:32,846 --> 00:57:33,889
I told you to wait for me.

1034
00:57:33,972 --> 00:57:35,682
It is your feet that are slow.

1035
00:57:35,766 --> 00:57:38,018
I have saved us good seats.
Sit down quickly.

1036
00:57:38,101 --> 00:57:39,436
What?

1037
00:57:39,519 --> 00:57:41,480
These aren't our seats. Get up.

1038
00:57:41,563 --> 00:57:44,066
They are not?
Then where are our seats?

1039
00:57:44,149 --> 00:57:45,108
Come on. Let's go.

1040
00:57:49,362 --> 00:57:51,281
Those seats over there
were nice and roomy.

1041
00:57:51,364 --> 00:57:52,532
Why is it so cramped here?

1042
00:57:52,616 --> 00:57:54,284
Because that was business class.

1043
00:57:54,367 --> 00:57:55,702
This is economy.

1044
00:57:55,786 --> 00:57:58,080
You could've just paid extra
if you liked it that much.

1045
00:57:58,163 --> 00:58:00,082
So they divide the seats based on money?

1046
00:58:00,791 --> 00:58:02,084
Is that what you are saying?

1047
00:58:02,167 --> 00:58:03,376
This wretched Hell Joseon.

1048
00:58:03,460 --> 00:58:04,628
Let's keep it moving.

1049
00:58:04,711 --> 00:58:06,588
-Sorry.
-What are they even doing?

1050
00:58:06,671 --> 00:58:09,216
-Hurry up and sit down. Just sit.
-So cramped.

1051
00:58:09,966 --> 00:58:10,842
Miserable bastards.

1052
00:58:10,926 --> 00:58:12,677
Why not make it clear from the start?

1053
00:58:12,761 --> 00:58:14,262
Beggars, commoners, and noblemen.

1054
00:58:14,346 --> 00:58:16,056
They might as well label the sections.

1055
00:58:16,139 --> 00:58:20,685
Listen, I've been meaning to
ask you something for a while now.

1056
00:58:20,769 --> 00:58:23,355
Did you actually finish
your compulsory education?

1057
00:58:23,438 --> 00:58:26,441
Because your English seems a bit lacking.

1058
00:58:27,317 --> 00:58:29,194
I am fluent in the language
of the mainland.

1059
00:58:29,277 --> 00:58:31,446
I have mastered
both the Sohak and the Analects.

1060
00:58:32,197 --> 00:58:34,491
Right. So your English is lacking.

1061
00:58:45,377 --> 00:58:46,670
Sir,

1062
00:58:46,753 --> 00:58:49,131
your recent insomnia
is work-related, right?

1063
00:58:49,214 --> 00:58:50,966
Or maybe something shifted personally?

1064
00:58:51,049 --> 00:58:52,342
Why?

1065
00:58:52,425 --> 00:58:54,719
Did Grandfather call you in
and grill you again?

1066
00:58:54,803 --> 00:58:57,472
No, sir. Nothing like that happened.

1067
00:58:57,556 --> 00:58:58,974
You won't be grilled anymore.

1068
00:58:59,057 --> 00:59:01,017
I decided to grant his wish, remember?

1069
00:59:01,101 --> 00:59:03,395
Why did you suddenly change your mind?

1070
00:59:03,478 --> 00:59:04,604
You said you were too busy.

1071
00:59:04,688 --> 00:59:06,565
Well, I found a need
for it myself as well.

1072
00:59:06,648 --> 00:59:08,024
It's a win-win situation.

1073
00:59:08,650 --> 00:59:10,944
It's a bit hot in here, though.

1074
00:59:12,737 --> 00:59:13,780
Is it just me?

1075
00:59:19,995 --> 00:59:21,496
I need to move around a bit.

1076
00:59:22,581 --> 00:59:23,456
Excuse me.

1077
00:59:24,249 --> 00:59:26,459
-Could he get a glass of cold water?
-Right away.

1078
00:59:31,298 --> 00:59:32,465
Goodness.

1079
00:59:33,800 --> 00:59:35,218
Jeez.

1080
00:59:35,844 --> 00:59:38,763
Please just sit still.
The person in front is staring.

1081
00:59:38,847 --> 00:59:41,683
It feels like I paid money to be tortured.

1082
00:59:41,766 --> 00:59:43,351
I would rather have my legs twisted.

1083
00:59:43,435 --> 00:59:45,228
Did you only ever fly business class?

1084
00:59:45,312 --> 00:59:46,771
Just hang in there.

1085
00:59:46,855 --> 00:59:49,149
I'm going to use the restroom.

1086
00:59:49,900 --> 00:59:51,193
Shoot!

1087
00:59:51,276 --> 00:59:53,570
You scoundrel! You wretched scoundrel!

1088
00:59:53,653 --> 00:59:55,280
Pardon me. Sorry.

1089
00:59:55,906 --> 00:59:58,074
I was thrilled to fly through the skies,

1090
00:59:58,158 --> 01:00:00,368
only to find myself tied down
and imprisoned.

1091
01:00:01,536 --> 01:00:03,079
Gosh. It's so stifling.

1092
01:00:06,416 --> 01:00:08,001
May I have your attention please?

1093
01:00:08,084 --> 01:00:09,836
We have a medical emergency on board.

1094
01:00:09,920 --> 01:00:12,130
Any medical professionals,
please see a flight attendant.

1095
01:00:12,214 --> 01:00:13,548
Thank you.

1096
01:00:15,342 --> 01:00:16,635
Any doctors or nurses?

1097
01:00:16,718 --> 01:00:18,345
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1098
01:00:18,428 --> 01:00:19,471
Any doctors or nurses?

1099
01:00:19,554 --> 01:00:21,139
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1100
01:00:22,349 --> 01:00:24,267
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1101
01:00:28,063 --> 01:00:28,980
A doctor?

1102
01:00:29,064 --> 01:00:30,982
We really appreciate you stepping up.

1103
01:00:32,776 --> 01:00:35,695
We were so worried.
Thank goodness we had a doctor on board.

1104
01:00:35,779 --> 01:00:37,405
You say a life is in grave danger.

1105
01:00:37,489 --> 01:00:40,695
It is man's duty to preserve
even the life of his enemy.

1106
01:00:40,784 --> 01:00:41,785
Eastern medicine?

1107
01:00:41,868 --> 01:00:44,204
I am known for my healing hands.

1108
01:00:44,287 --> 01:00:45,830
Even during my palace maid days,

1109
01:00:45,914 --> 01:00:48,875
palace nurses lined up for me to prick
their fingers to relieve indigestion.

1110
01:00:48,959 --> 01:00:50,460
One, two, three, four.

1111
01:00:50,543 --> 01:00:51,670
-Right here.
-Five, six.

1112
01:00:51,753 --> 01:00:53,797
-The doctor is here.
-Seven, eight. Three, two, three.

1113
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:54,965
Six, seven, eight.

1114
01:00:55,048 --> 01:00:55,924
Cha Se-gye?

1115
01:00:57,634 --> 01:00:58,885
Hey, Cha Se-gye!

1116
01:00:58,969 --> 01:01:00,387
Why are you sprawled out like this?

1117
01:01:00,470 --> 01:01:02,264
Do you know him? Thank goodness.

1118
01:01:02,973 --> 01:01:04,683
Pricking his finger will not be enough.

1119
01:01:05,684 --> 01:01:06,977
Cha Se-gye, breathe. Come on.

1120
01:01:07,060 --> 01:01:08,103
Cha Se-gye!

1121
01:01:08,186 --> 01:01:09,980
What are you doing? Please start CPR!

1122
01:01:10,063 --> 01:01:11,106
What? "Sipper"?

1123
01:01:11,189 --> 01:01:12,274
Hold on.

1124
01:01:12,357 --> 01:01:14,109
Oh no…

1125
01:01:14,192 --> 01:01:16,194
Come on, Cha Se-gye!

1126
01:01:16,278 --> 01:01:17,529
Breathe, come on!

1127
01:01:17,612 --> 01:01:18,905
Cha Se-gye!

1128
01:01:22,909 --> 01:01:25,287
Passengers, the aircraft
is experiencing turbulence…

1129
01:01:25,370 --> 01:01:26,871
What are you doing? Hurry!

1130
01:01:26,955 --> 01:01:29,040
Please fasten your seatbelts.

1131
01:01:30,125 --> 01:01:31,793
Ladies and gentlemen…

1132
01:01:34,170 --> 01:01:35,839
What the…

1133
01:01:35,922 --> 01:01:37,549
What are you doing right now?

1134
01:01:38,174 --> 01:01:39,259
Cha Se-gye!

1135
01:01:39,342 --> 01:01:41,636
Cha Se-gye, wake up!

1136
01:01:41,720 --> 01:01:43,221
Wake up!

1137
01:01:43,305 --> 01:01:44,848
Cha Se-gye!

1138
01:01:46,057 --> 01:01:47,976
Come on, Cha Se-gye!

1139
01:01:57,444 --> 01:01:58,778
Cha Se-gye.

1140
01:01:58,862 --> 01:02:00,989
Are you finally coming to your senses?

1141
01:02:02,157 --> 01:02:05,994
Goodness, I really thought you were
about to cross into the afterlife.

1142
01:02:08,288 --> 01:02:09,581
You…

1143
01:02:11,166 --> 01:02:13,293
-Poison…
-What poison?

1144
01:02:14,002 --> 01:02:15,545
Tonic? Toxin?

1145
01:02:15,628 --> 01:02:17,714
I cannot hear you. Speak up!

1146
01:02:18,340 --> 01:02:19,549
Rat poison.

1147
01:02:19,632 --> 01:02:20,884
Rat poison?

1148
01:02:27,140 --> 01:02:29,059
You're toxic, like poison.

1149
01:02:34,564 --> 01:02:36,775
Cha Se-gye!

1150
01:02:37,400 --> 01:02:38,526
Have you gone mad?

1151
01:02:38,610 --> 01:02:39,694
Cha Se-gye!

1152
01:02:39,778 --> 01:02:42,989
Open your eyes! Cha Se-gye!

1153
01:02:43,698 --> 01:02:45,658
Cha Se-gye!

1154
01:02:45,742 --> 01:02:46,659
Where's the AED?

1155
01:02:47,285 --> 01:02:48,453
I have it.

1156
01:02:48,953 --> 01:02:52,082
No! Don't die, Cha Se-gye!

1157
01:02:52,165 --> 01:02:54,000
Cha Se-gye!

1158
01:03:00,673 --> 01:03:02,467
Cha Se-gye!

1159
01:03:02,550 --> 01:03:03,510
You cannot die!

1160
01:03:03,593 --> 01:03:06,221
Cha Se-gye, do not leave me!

1161
01:03:06,304 --> 01:03:08,681
No, please do not die!

1162
01:03:08,765 --> 01:03:10,975
-Everyone, step back.
-No, do not die!

1163
01:03:11,059 --> 01:03:13,395
-Cha Se-gye, no!
-One, two, three!

1164
01:03:13,478 --> 01:03:14,813
No--

1165
01:03:28,076 --> 01:03:28,952
Oh no…

1166
01:03:29,869 --> 01:03:31,121
My welfare is my first priority.

1167
01:03:31,204 --> 01:03:33,081
And my second.

1168
01:03:33,164 --> 01:03:36,251
In this life, I will be sure
to guard my heart

1169
01:03:36,334 --> 01:03:37,836
and live out my days to the fullest.

1170
01:03:58,857 --> 01:04:02,402
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1171
01:04:04,446 --> 01:04:05,655
Here.

1172
01:04:22,964 --> 01:04:25,008
Become my brother's lover.

1173
01:04:41,149 --> 01:04:43,651
You must have cherished this dog greatly.

1174
01:04:43,735 --> 01:04:45,820
I am sure it is grateful.

1175
01:04:48,072 --> 01:04:49,365
Thanks to you,

1176
01:04:49,449 --> 01:04:52,243
its life here was a little less lonely.

1177
01:05:00,043 --> 01:05:01,419
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

1178
01:05:03,463 --> 01:05:05,006
This flower suits you.

1179
01:05:05,089 --> 01:05:07,926
It stands out, so it is perfect for you.

1180
01:05:15,016 --> 01:05:17,143
Do not be too heartbroken.

1181
01:05:17,727 --> 01:05:22,273
Why not seek out a true companion
instead of a dog that cannot speak?

1182
01:05:22,357 --> 01:05:23,566
Shall I be

1183
01:05:23,650 --> 01:05:25,026
that companion for you?

1184
01:06:16,911 --> 01:06:19,664
Have I finally crossed over
to the afterlife?

1185
01:06:19,747 --> 01:06:22,166
Could this be paradise?

1186
01:06:22,250 --> 01:06:25,712
If I am doing this, I might as well
go all out and show it all off.

1187
01:06:25,795 --> 01:06:28,214
Change her outfit. Next. Swap.

1188
01:06:28,298 --> 01:06:29,716
Are your eyes possessed or something?

1189
01:06:29,799 --> 01:06:31,884
She's the only thing I can see right now!

1190
01:06:32,719 --> 01:06:34,721
Why are you nitpicking
every little thing today?

1191
01:06:34,804 --> 01:06:37,724
Just because I rejected your affections,
you hound me all damn day?

1192
01:06:37,807 --> 01:06:39,642
I am truly glad to be alive.

1193
01:06:39,726 --> 01:06:40,893
Drink up!

1194
01:06:40,977 --> 01:06:43,438
It seems the time has come.
Take care of her quietly.

1195
01:06:43,521 --> 01:06:45,273
Is Seo-ri still not answering?

1196
01:06:45,857 --> 01:06:47,692
You saw her? Where?

1197
01:06:47,775 --> 01:06:49,652
Where is she right now?

1198
01:06:53,031 --> 01:06:55,033
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
